President Obama spoke with President Erdogan of Turkey to discuss their ongoing cooperation in the fight against ISIL and their efforts to bring stability to Iraq and a political settlement to the conflict in Syria. They condemned recent terrorist attacks in Turkey and expressed condolences to the families of the victims. The leaders also discussed increasing cooperation to prevent the flow of foreign fighters and secure Turkey's border with Syria. President Obama reassured Turkey of the United States' commitment to their national security, and both leaders pledged to continue working closely on regional issues.